**overcome ssl handshake error**

    System.setProperty(&quot;https.protocols&quot;, &quot;TLSv1,TLSv1.1,TLSv1.2&quot;);

This error is generic of the security libraries and might happen in other cases.
In case other people have this same error when sending emails with javax.mail to a smtp server. Then the code to force other protocol is setting a property like this:

    prop.put(&quot;mail.smtp.ssl.protocols&quot;, &quot;TLSv1.2&quot;);            

    //And just in case probably you need to set these too
    prop.put(&quot;mail.smtp.starttls.enable&quot;, true);    
    prop.put(&quot;mail.smtp.ssl.trust&quot;, {YOURSERVERNAME});

In my case i was making a request to a system that is using SSLV3.
So i have added the following jvm option. And problem got resolved.

    -Dhttps.protocols=&quot;TLSv1,TLSv1.1,TLSv1.2&quot;

